# TLD 
-> Test last development
 coding is completed ie dev.-> tests are created -> tests are executed

# TDD
-> Test driven development
test created-> tests executes(fails no code)-> write code to pass test -> refactor test to remove redundancy

# BDD
->extension of TDD
->like tdd we write test first and application code
-> only differences betn them is bdd explains behaviour of application and are  more user-focused as it uses user stories.
-> documentation is written is shared language called gherkin

# example of login features
feature - login
userstory - as a user when i enter valid credentials i should be able to login and enter home page

same story in gherkin looks like this: 
feature : check login functionality
scenario: give user is on login page -->prerequisitee
when user enters valid credits -->Action

and clicks on login button --> some more action
navigated to homepage --> expected

